{"word":"H5596 - סָפַח - çâphach - saw-fakh' - Abiding","slug":"H5596","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">סָפַח</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>çâphach"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>saw-fakh'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Abiding"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C2;&#x05E4;&#x05D7;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E1;&#x05E4;&#x05D7; - sa&#x0302;phach  s&#x0301;a&#x0302;phach</b> - <i>saw-fakh', saw-fakh'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>scrape</i> out, but in certain peculiar senses (of <i>removal</i> or <i>association</i>): - abiding, gather together, cleave, put, smite with a scab."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4555\">H4555</a>, <a href=\"#/H4556\">H4556</a>, <a href=\"#/H5597\">H5597</a>, <a href=\"#/H5601\">H5601</a>, <a href=\"#/H5602\">H5602</a>"}]}